  "texts": [
    "The eect on w is hump-shaped: there is a threshold I * (K/L) with Φ(I * (•)) ∈ (0, 1) such that wages w rise in Φ(I) as long as I < I * (K/L) or, equivalently, as long as K/L > κ * (I), but decline in Φ(I) for I > I * (K/L) or, equivalently, K/L < κ * (I).",
    "(ii) For Φ(I) = 0, the return on capital is R = 0, and wages equal w = A.",
    "For Φ(I) ≥ κ/(1 + κ), both equal R = w = A.",
    "The latter condition always holds if Φ(I) = 1.",
    "The limit results follow readily from equations (6) and (7) and from the second part of Lemma 1."
  ],
